title.narrative: 105/004 Coss Sectoral Costs

description.narrative: 2021 has been the last year of the 2017–2021 extended;country;programme. The office did not undertake any major change in the management structure and work arrangements of the cross-sectoral costs;which;continued to play a strategic role in supporting the implementation of programme activities. Following an affordability analysis of cross-sectoral costs conducted during the second quarter of 2020,;the CMT approved an increase of the contribution of grants towards the cross-sectoral;from;four;to;eight per cent. Despite this critical decision,;donor contributions to support the implementation of cross-sectoral activities remained low during the reporting period. | Status:Met | As-of Date:23/12/2021
